task.summary:
Update gradle and A3Droid jar
* android version 24 * java version 1.8 (enabled jack option)

some comments to ui: start of experiment and so on...
Sensor followers role and sensor supervisor role: send all the RTTs back to supervisor each sensor sends all the
Test Group initialization: testClass to measure the time that is required to shape one group

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/deib-polimi/A3Droid_TestApp
# Conflicts: # a3Test_Greenhouse/libs/A3Droid.jar # a3Test_Greenhouse/src/androidTest/java/it/polimi/greenhouse/TestDeviceBehavior.java # a3Test_Greenhouse/src/main/java/it/polimi/greenhouse/activities/MainActivity.java # a3Test_Greenhouse/src/main/res/layout/activity_main.xml # build.gradle

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/deib-polimi/A3Droid_TestApp
# Conflicts: # a3Test_Greenhouse/libs/A3Droid.jar # a3Test_Greenhouse/src/androidTest/java/it/polimi/greenhouse/TestDeviceBehavior.java # a3Test_Greenhouse/src/main/java/it/polimi/greenhouse/activities/MainActivity.java # a3Test_Greenhouse/src/main/res/layout/activity_main.xml # build.gradle

TestGroupAccession, supervisor testtime increased to wait more for followers to write back test results.
TestNewSupervisorElection: for robustnes testing to measure recovery ability by electing a new supervisor in case of unavaiability of the current supervisor
TestLoadTesting Experiment: Having The number of followers of a given group fixed, we invrease the messsages/sec rate and message size independently sent form followers to supervisor and measured the RTT of ACK message back to followers from supervisor.--- still implementing
ControllFollowerRole: postUIEvent(0, "[CtrlFolRole]"); line removed not to show multiple lines of , "[CtrlFolRole]" in EditBox.
SensorSpervisor Role: node.connect("server_0"); line commented out
MainActivity: sensorSupervisorRole and sensorFollowerRole added for each node to make the node able to be the supervisor and follower of the group. This currently is used to implement newSupervisorElection Test.
Load testing added, still working on it
